title: For Sale:  Ruger 0915 Bearcat Shopkeeper RUKSBCBH-3
postcontent:
MAKE: Ruger
MODEL: Bearcat Shopkeeper
SKU NUMBER: 0915
STOCK NUMBER: RUKSBCBH-3 Lipsey Exclusive
CALIBER: 22 LR
STOCK STYLE & FINISH: Stainless Finish w/ Wood Grips
BARREL FINISH: Stainless
BARREL LENGTH: 3”
CAPACITY: 6
WEIGHT: 22oz.
OVERALL LENGTH: 8”
SIGHTS: Fixed
TWIST: 1:16
EXTRAS: Birdshead Gripframe, Crescent Ejector Rod, Button Head Cylinder Pin,

Some Lipsey Exclusive guns happen fairly fast, others take some time. The Bearcat Shopkeeper is one gun that has been on the drawing table for several years. It all started with a visit by Lipsey to one of our biggest and most loyal dealers in Alabama. He showed them a beautiful little 3" barreled Ruger Bearcat. Everyone agreed it would make for a great Lipsey's Exclusive, and after talking to Ruger, they agreed to take a look at it.
Ruger decided to produce a round butt or birdshead type frame to go along with the 3" barrel. In addition to the 3" barrel and birdshead gripframe, they had to use a couple of other unique features to make it all work. Due to the short barrel, Ruger had to use a "button head" cylinder pin and a crescent shape ejector rod so that the spent cases could easily be extracted from the cylinder. Ruger is also using a steel ejector rod housing that matches the rest of the gun verses the aluminum one used on the standard Bearcats.
Even though it took 3 years, the wonderful engineers at Ruger made it happen and now we have a true "Shopkeeper" size Ruger Bearcat.
This is one of those guns that once you put it in your hands, you will have to get one.

Cedar Hill, Mo.63016

title: For Trade:  MKA 1919 Semi Auto mag fed 12G shotgun
postcontent: The Akdal MKA 1919 is a gas operated, semi-automatic shotgun that resembles the M16 rifle and mimics the layout and placement of some of the controls. It was created by Turkish company Akdal Arms. The MKA 1919 uses a conventional gas-operated action which is located around the support tube that runs below the barrel. The return spring is also located around the same support tube which is concealed by an enlarged polymer handguard. The MKA 1919 barrel can be quickly removed from upper receiver. To charge the rifle, the charging handle on the receiver must be pulled. The upper receiver is manufactured from an aluminum alloy while the lower receiver, along with pistol grip and shoulder stock, is manufactured as one piece from impact-resistant polymer. Akdal MKA 1919 semi-automatic rifle has a 5 round detachable box magazine. It has a bolt release identical in location and function to the one on the M16. Manual safety also duplicates M16-style being located on the left side of the receiver above the pistol grip.[2] Standard sights include a front post installed on the M16-style removable base and a detachable M16A2-style carrying handle with built-in diopter sight. On the upper receiver, an integral Picatinny rail can be placed which will accept detachable carrying handle or optional red-dot or other optical sight attachments.

The grip and stock are easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. Fast and Accurate Shooting

Maximized Safety Systems

1. Trigger Safety
The two-piece trigger prevents the weapon from firing without a presure on the trigger.

2. Firing Pin Safety
The firing pin safety prevents the stricker from passing.
The firing pin safety is lifted out the way when the trigger is pulled.

 3. Drop Safety
Part of the fire control housing prevents the sear from rotating down to release the stricker unless the trigger is pulled.

I also have the paperwork and box for the CT grip with cleaning tips and allens for adjusting windage and elevation, as well as the OEM pin that the CT replaces in the grip. **Not willing to travel more than maybe an hour away, no shipping, PA residents preferred,  and face to face only.
